(1) For a first offense, an additional $25.
(2) For a second offense, an additional $50.
(3) For a third offense, an additional $100.
(4) For a fourth or subsequent offense, an additional $250.
Proposed law repeals these additional fines.
Effective upon signature of governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
(Repeals R.S. 14:98.1(A)(4), 98.2(A)(5), 98.3(A)(4), and 98.4(A)(3))
